newsitem.title: USA: Trade sees increase in weekly U.S. corn exports.
newsitem.headline: Trade sees increase in weekly U.S. corn exports.

text.p: The U.S. Agriculture Department's weekly export sales data, to be released at 0730 CST/1330 GMT Thursday, was expected to show U.S. corn was sold for export at a more rapid pace the week ended December 12 than in the previous week, trade sources said.
Net export sales for corn during the week ended December 12 were expected from 700,000 to 900,000 tonnes, above the previous week's tally of 507,900 tonnes.
Wheat net export sales were seen at 300,000 to 400,000 tonnes, nearly the same as the 346,200 the previous week.

Soybean exports were expected from 500,000 to 600,000 tonnes, slightly below the 645,400 the previous week. Soyoil sales were pegged at 10,000 to 20,000 tonnes compared with 42,700 the previous week and soymeal sales were estimated at 100,000 to 200,000 tonnes, about the same as the previous week's tally of 147,200 tonnes.
